00:42:15,116 --> 00:42:16,948
Dr. Shaw.

526
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:19,742
How did she end up here?

527
00:42:23,374 --> 00:42:25,081
Sergeant Lope,
can I get a light on this?

528
00:42:25,251 --> 00:42:26,741
- Over here.
- Be careful.

529
00:42:26,919 --> 00:42:27,909
Yeah.

530
00:42:30,423 --> 00:42:31,458
Wow.

531
00:42:31,591 --> 00:42:32,581
Jesus.

532
00:42:35,887 --> 00:42:37,469
Oram, behind you. Move.

533
00:42:49,817 --> 00:42:51,558
<i>Home</i>

534
00:42:51,736 --> 00:42:54,649
<i>Take me home</i>

535
00:42:54,822 --> 00:42:57,109
<i>To the place</i>

536
00:42:59,494 --> 00:43:00,780
<i>West Virginia...</i>

537
00:43:02,121 --> 00:43:03,327
<i>mountain momma</i>

538
00:43:03,498 --> 00:43:04,829
I think we found our source.

539
00:43:08,127 --> 00:43:09,242
Yeah.

540
00:43:11,464 --> 00:43:13,171
What the hell was she doing
out here?

541
00:43:15,343 --> 00:43:17,300
Poor thing.

542
00:43:23,518 --> 00:43:24,804
I have to sit down.

543
00:43:25,353 --> 00:43:27,014
I have to sit down.

544
00:43:27,855 --> 00:43:29,266
I'm sorry.

545
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:31,272
I don't know what's wrong with me.

546
00:43:31,442 --> 00:43:33,353
Just look at me.

547
00:43:35,863 --> 00:43:36,944
I can't breathe.

548
00:43:38,658 --> 00:43:39,773
Stay calm.

549
00:43:41,327 --> 00:43:42,783
I'll be right back.

550
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:47,367
Captain Oram. Come in.

551
00:43:48,626 --> 00:43:50,208
<i>Come in.
Chris, it's Karine.</i>

552
00:43:50,670 --> 00:43:51,660
What? Yes?

553
00:43:51,838 --> 00:43:53,374
<i>We have an issue.</i>

554
00:43:53,548 --> 00:43:56,711
<i>We're heading back to the Lander.
Repeat. We're returning to the Lander.</i>

555
00:43:56,884 --> 00:43:58,716
Is everything okay?

556
00:43:58,886 --> 00:44:01,719
<i>Ledward is sick. We're heading back.</i>

557
00:44:01,889 --> 00:44:04,722
<i>Faris, you get that?
Prep the Med Bay, okay?</i>

558
00:44:04,892 --> 00:44:05,882
Will do, Karine. What's going on?

559
00:44:06,060 --> 00:44:08,051
<i>Please, just do it.
We'll be there soon.</i>

560
00:44:08,229 --> 00:44:09,515
<i>Daniels, come in.</i>

561
00:44:09,689 --> 00:44:11,396
<i>We're heading back.</i>

562
00:44:14,193 --> 00:44:15,479
<i>- What's going on?
- I don't know.</i>

563
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:17,064
It's something about Ledward.

564
00:44:19,198 --> 00:44:21,781
They're coming. Let's move.

565
00:44:26,581 --> 00:44:28,492
- Guys!
- Tom!

566
00:44:28,666 --> 00:44:31,249
What's going on, man?
Are you all right?

567
00:44:31,419 --> 00:44:33,456
Talk to me. Look at me.

568
00:44:33,629 --> 00:44:35,540
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

569
00:44:35,715 --> 00:44:37,547
- Can you walk?
- Yeah.

570
00:44:37,717 --> 00:44:40,004
Okay, let's go.
Let's get the fuck out of here.

571
00:44:40,178 --> 00:44:41,543
All right.

572
00:44:43,264 --> 00:44:46,006
Babe, are we talking
quarantine protocols?

573
00:44:46,184 --> 00:44:50,098
<i>I don't know, but she said that
Ledward was bleeding...</i>

574
00:44:50,271 --> 00:44:51,932
and to prepare the Med Bay.

575
00:44:52,106 --> 00:44:53,221
Bleeding?

576
00:44:53,399 --> 00:44:55,606
<i>Yeah, I know, that's what I thought...</i>

577
00:44:55,776 --> 00:44:58,438
Faris, you're breaking up.
We can't hear you, can you repeat?

578
00:44:58,613 --> 00:45:01,696
<i>I don't know from what,
I don't know how serious it is.</i>

579
00:45:01,866 --> 00:45:03,482
<i>She sounded scared.</i>

580
00:45:03,659 --> 00:45:06,117
<i>Paris, where are you?
Come on, I need your help!</i>

581
00:45:08,372 --> 00:45:10,158
Faris, where are you?

582
00:45:10,333 --> 00:45:12,165
We're here. Come in!

583
00:45:13,461 --> 00:45:15,293
- Ledward, come on.
- I can't.

584
00:45:15,463 --> 00:45:18,706
Almost there, you see?
Straight ahead.

585
00:45:18,883 --> 00:45:21,625
Faris! Get over here!

586
00:45:21,802 --> 00:45:23,418
Come on, I need your help!

587
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:35,930
Fucking help me!

588
00:45:38,277 --> 00:45:39,392
Help me.

589
00:45:43,991 --> 00:45:45,197
Stay up, Ledward.

590
00:45:47,411 --> 00:45:48,526
Get him to the Med Bay...

591
00:45:48,704 --> 00:45:50,160
<i>and touch nothing on your way through.</i>

592
00:45:53,793 --> 00:45:56,581
Faris, get over here!
Come on!

593
00:45:57,380 --> 00:45:58,495
Go!

594
00:45:58,673 --> 00:46:00,084
Up, up!

595
00:46:00,967 --> 00:46:02,002
Ledward, you gotta stay up!

596
00:46:02,176 --> 00:46:03,382
Oram, where are you?

597
00:46:03,552 --> 00:46:04,792
<i>We are on our way back.</i>

598
00:46:04,971 --> 00:46:05,836
How long?

599
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:08,220
It's not long now.
We're almost there.

600
00:46:10,142 --> 00:46:11,507
No! Stay up!

601
00:46:15,147 --> 00:46:17,514
Fuck! Fuck! Okay.

602
00:46:19,235 --> 00:46:20,350
Come to the table!

603
00:46:21,946 --> 00:46:24,108
Up! Up!

604
00:46:24,782 --> 00:46:25,772
Come on, Ledward!

605
00:46:25,950 --> 00:46:27,361
Come on! That's it!

606
00:46:30,079 --> 00:46:32,867
<i>Karine, put some gloves on.
Don't touch anything!</i>

607
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:34,826
<i>- Stop saying that!</i>
- Faris!

608
00:46:35,001 --> 00:46:35,866
<i>He already puked all over me!</i>

609
00:46:36,043 --> 00:46:37,750
Faris, what's going on?

610
00:46:46,971 --> 00:46:49,008
Just stay here. I'm gonna get Oram.

611
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:02,600
Oram, I need you back here right now.

612
00:47:02,778 --> 00:47:05,110
I need you to come back
to the Lander right now!

613
00:47:05,281 --> 00:47:07,943
I understand that,
but we are moving as fast as we can.

614
00:47:10,536 --> 00:47:13,494
Come on, get up.
We're almost there.

615
00:47:13,664 --> 00:47:16,406
<i>I don't know what the fuck is wrong
with Ledward.</i>

616
00:47:16,584 --> 00:47:20,077
He started bleeding, <i>he's</i> sick,
I don't know what the fuck to do.

617
00:47:20,838 --> 00:47:22,670
Just calm down, sweetheart.
Tell me what's happening.

618
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:24,706
<i>Don't tell me to fucking calm down!</i>

619
00:47:24,884 --> 00:47:26,124
<i>You didn't just see what I saw.</i>

620
00:47:26,302 --> 00:47:30,717
<i>I don't know what the fuck Ledward got
or if Karine's got it or if I have it!</i>

621
00:47:30,890 --> 00:47:32,597
- Tee!
<i>- Faris!</i>

622
00:47:32,767 --> 00:47:33,723
Come in!

623
00:47:33,893 --> 00:47:35,725
Faris, where are you?

624
00:47:35,895 --> 00:47:37,556
I need to I.V. him!

625
00:47:39,815 --> 00:47:41,431
Don't you know how to work
this fucking thing?

626
00:47:41,609 --> 00:47:43,520
Fucking yelling doesn't help anything!

627
00:47:45,321 --> 00:47:47,779
- Let me out.
- Oram is coming.

628
00:47:48,532 --> 00:47:50,273
- Let me the fuck out.
- We're gonna wait...

629
00:47:50,451 --> 00:47:52,158
Faris, please. Open up!

630
00:47:52,328 --> 00:47:55,446
I can't do that.
I have to keep the infection local.

631
00:48:10,096 --> 00:48:12,633
Let me the fuck out!
Let me the fuck out!

632
00:48:16,018 --> 00:48:17,008
Faris!

633
00:48:17,561 --> 00:48:19,677
Fuck you, Faris! Open up!

634
00:48:21,148 --> 00:48:22,855
Open up the fucking door!

635
00:48:25,945 --> 00:48:27,606
Let me the fuck out!

636
00:48:31,951 --> 00:48:34,943
Let me out! Faris, you fuck!

637
00:48:55,891 --> 00:48:56,847
Faris!

638
00:48:58,018 --> 00:48:59,258
I'm coming!

639
00:49:00,813 --> 00:49:01,894
Oh, God...

640
00:49:02,064 --> 00:49:03,975
Please hurry,
there's something on board.

641
00:49:04,150 --> 00:49:06,266
Go again, you're breaking up.

642
00:49:06,944 --> 00:49:08,935
Lander One, repeat.

643
00:49:09,655 --> 00:49:13,114
<i>Lander One, repeat!
Lander One, repeat!</i>

644
00:49:16,704 --> 00:49:18,286
Stay the fuck away!

645
00:49:32,553 --> 00:49:34,635
No! Karine!

646
00:50:34,198 --> 00:50:35,404
Fucker!

647
00:50:44,333 --> 00:50:45,869
- Oh, my God!
- Karine! Hold on!

648
00:50:50,756 --> 00:50:52,372
Captain! Get down!

649
00:50:52,883 --> 00:50:54,339
No! No!

650
00:51:07,606 --> 00:51:09,096
- Guys, hold him down!
- Talk to me!

651
00:51:15,823 --> 00:51:17,063
Oh, my God.

652
00:51:22,997 --> 00:51:24,032
Stay down.

653
00:51:31,672 --> 00:51:32,707
Help me! Hold him!

654
00:51:38,178 --> 00:51:39,589
What the fuck!

655
00:52:04,788 --> 00:52:08,782
It's a 7.5 ion storm, it's a miracle
we talked to them for as long as we could.

656
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:11,075
Then we'll fly through it.

657
00:52:11,253 --> 00:52:12,709
We cannot do that, Tennessee.

658
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:14,712
You're a pilot,
you know what the tolerances are.

659
00:52:14,882 --> 00:52:16,498
Fuck the tolerances.

660
00:52:16,675 --> 00:52:17,506
Tee...

661
00:52:17,676 --> 00:52:20,338
it's a goddamn hurricane down there,
we would break up.

662
00:52:21,221 --> 00:52:23,462
We just have to wait it out.

663
00:52:24,391 --> 00:52:25,552
I'm sorry, Tee.

664
00:52:27,061 --> 00:52:28,643
She was scared.

665
00:52:29,104 --> 00:52:31,766
Never heard my wife scared before.

666
00:52:32,399 --> 00:52:34,891
<i>Covenant?</i> Come in.

667
00:52:36,362 --> 00:52:38,820
<i>Covenant.</i> Do you read me?

668
00:52:39,490 --> 00:52:40,776
<i>Covenant.</i>

669
00:52:40,949 --> 00:52:42,940
<i>Covenant,</i> do you read me?

670
00:52:45,954 --> 00:52:46,944
<i>Covenant,</i> come in.

671
00:52:47,122 --> 00:52:48,328
I'll always be with you.

672
00:52:49,792 --> 00:52:50,873
Light of my life.

673
00:52:51,043 --> 00:52:52,499
<i>Covenant,</i> do you read me?

674
00:52:52,670 --> 00:52:54,411
My love, my angel.

675
00:52:54,588 --> 00:52:57,296
Lope, there's nothing you can do.

676
00:52:59,343 --> 00:53:01,129
There's nothing, okay?

677
00:53:02,137 --> 00:53:03,878
<i>Covenant,</i> do you read me?

678
00:53:07,935 --> 00:53:10,097
- Tennessee, come in for fuck's sake!
- Daniels!

679
00:53:10,270 --> 00:53:11,385
Look out!

680
00:53:15,192 --> 00:53:16,023
Move! Move!

681
00:53:23,951 --> 00:53:25,112
- Fire!
- Shoot! Go!

682
00:53:26,370 --> 00:53:27,576
Daniels, get down!

683
00:53:33,544 --> 00:53:34,454
Ankor, no!

684
00:53:36,797 --> 00:53:37,787
Go, Cole!

685
00:53:40,300 --> 00:53:41,461
I got him!

686
00:53:41,635 --> 00:53:43,546
- Daniels, are you okay?
- Yeah!

687
00:53:43,721 --> 00:53:44,927
What the fuck was that?

688
00:53:45,472 --> 00:53:46,462
We are okay.

689
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:49,298
There's another one!
Get out of the way!

690
00:53:49,476 --> 00:53:50,466
Behind you!

691
00:53:50,644 --> 00:53:51,975
- I'm jammed!
- Look out!

692
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:55,304
Get off me!

693
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:57,640
I can't get a clean shot!

694
00:53:57,818 --> 00:53:59,104
Get off!

695
00:54:26,263 --> 00:54:27,503
Follow me.

696
00:54:31,018 --> 00:54:32,349
I'll get the captain.

697
00:54:33,854 --> 00:54:35,015
Ankor...

698
00:54:35,189 --> 00:54:36,350
Captain!

699
00:54:39,026 --> 00:54:41,267
Chris! Chris!

700
00:54:41,779 --> 00:54:44,146
We have to go now! We have to go.

701
00:54:45,032 --> 00:54:46,522
- Come on.
- Okay.

702
00:54:48,202 --> 00:54:50,193
- Come on.
- Okay.

703
00:55:08,680 --> 00:55:11,012
Let's go! Move it!

704
00:55:17,397 --> 00:55:18,853
Through here.

705
00:55:33,872 --> 00:55:34,862
What is this?

706
00:55:43,507 --> 00:55:44,463
Let's go.

707
00:55:44,633 --> 00:55:45,919
Come on, Captain.
We gotta keep moving.

708
00:55:47,261 --> 00:55:48,751
Jesus.

709
00:55:48,929 --> 00:55:49,919
What happened here?

710
00:55:50,097 --> 00:55:51,087
Keep it up.

711
00:56:06,488 --> 00:56:07,478
Let's go, let's go.

712
00:56:57,164 --> 00:56:58,529
My name is David.

713
00:56:59,166 --> 00:57:01,157
May I ask who's in charge here?

714
00:57:03,295 --> 00:57:05,036
May I ask who's in charge?

715
00:57:06,673 --> 00:57:08,163
Yes, I am the captain.

716
00:57:08,342 --> 00:57:09,878
What were those things?

717
00:57:10,052 --> 00:57:11,167
Is it even safe here?

718
00:57:12,971 --> 00:57:13,961
Perfectly.

719
00:57:14,556 --> 00:57:16,718
I'll explain as best I can.

720
00:57:18,393 --> 00:57:22,182
Ten years ago, Dr. Elizabeth Shaw and I
arrived here...

721
00:57:23,023 --> 00:57:25,060
the only survivors of the <i>Prometheus.</i>

722
00:57:26,526 --> 00:57:28,642
The ship we traveled on
carried a weapon.

723
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:30,686
A deadly virus.

724
00:57:30,864 --> 00:57:33,697
Payload accidentally deployed
when we were landing.

725
00:57:33,867 --> 00:57:37,155
In the confusion,
we lost control of the ship.

726
00:57:39,247 --> 00:57:40,988
Elizabeth died in the crash.

727
00:57:42,042 --> 00:57:43,908
You've seen the result of the pathogen.

728
00:57:46,546 --> 00:57:49,504
Thus, I've been marooned here
these many years.

729
00:57:51,510 --> 00:57:53,717
Crusoe on his island.

730
00:57:53,887 --> 00:57:56,219
Our crew was infected with this virus?

731
00:57:56,765 --> 00:58:01,350
The pathogen was designed
to infect all nonbotanical life forms.

732
00:58:01,520 --> 00:58:03,102
All the animals...

733
00:58:03,271 --> 00:58:04,727
the meat, if you will.

734
00:58:05,899 --> 00:58:08,231
Either kill them outright...

735
00:58:08,402 --> 00:58:10,769
or use them
as incubators to spawn a hybrid form.

736
00:58:10,946 --> 00:58:12,732
Highly aggressive.

737
00:58:13,240 --> 00:58:14,696
Have we been infected?

738
00:58:15,867 --> 00:58:17,778
You'd know by now.

739
00:58:17,953 --> 00:58:19,443
We have to be certain.

740
00:58:20,914 --> 00:58:23,076
We can't take this back to the ship.

741
00:58:23,250 --> 00:58:25,287
We're a colony mission.

742
00:58:26,086 --> 00:58:27,747
Really?

743
00:58:27,921 --> 00:58:29,753
How extraordinary.

744
00:58:31,675 --> 00:58:33,131
How many colonists?

745
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:37,128
Over two thousand.

746
00:58:37,305 --> 00:58:39,091
Well, well, well.

747
00:58:39,641 --> 00:58:41,427
So many good souls.

748
00:58:41,935 --> 00:58:43,096
Captain Oram.

749
00:58:43,687 --> 00:58:47,681
Field transmitters aren't going to
have a chance through all this stone.

750
00:58:49,317 --> 00:58:51,479
Is there a safe way to get to the roof?

751
00:58:51,862 --> 00:58:53,023
Assuredly.

752
00:58:53,697 --> 00:58:56,109
And please do make yourselves at home...

753
00:58:56,283 --> 00:58:59,992
as much as you're able
in this dire necropolis.

754
00:59:01,621 --> 00:59:02,656
Welcome, brother.

755
00:59:05,333 --> 00:59:06,323
This way.

756
00:59:09,379 --> 00:59:12,121
Everyone,
let's set up a staging area here.

757
00:59:17,304 --> 00:59:19,386
There's so much here
that doesn't make sense.

758
00:59:20,182 --> 00:59:21,798
I'll talk to him.

759
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:25,301
Brother to brother.

760
00:59:30,609 --> 00:59:32,065
Tennessee? Ricks?

761
00:59:32,235 --> 00:59:33,521
Come in! Do you copy?

762
00:59:35,614 --> 00:59:37,776
<i>Covenant,</i> come in.
This is Expedition Party reporting.

763
00:59:37,949 --> 00:59:39,735
Do you read me?

764
00:59:40,410 --> 00:59:41,821
Tennessee?

765
00:59:41,995 --> 00:59:43,986
Tennessee, Ricks, come in.

766
00:59:44,498 --> 00:59:47,581
I'm not sure they'll hear you
through the storm.

767
00:59:48,627 --> 00:59:50,789
They can be quite severe...

768
00:59:51,630 --> 00:59:52,916
shielding the whole planet.

769
00:59:54,091 --> 00:59:56,549
How long do the storms usually last?

770
00:59:57,552 --> 00:59:59,088
Days.

771
00:59:59,262 --> 01:00:00,343
Weeks.

772
01:00:01,014 --> 01:00:01,845
Months.

773
01:00:04,643 --> 01:00:06,054
But do keep at it.

774
01:00:07,479 --> 01:00:08,765
Best of luck.

775
01:00:11,024 --> 01:00:14,392
<i>Covenant,</i> this is Expedition Party
reporting. Come in.

776
01:00:15,445 --> 01:00:17,231
<i>Covenant,</i> come in.

777
01:00:17,823 --> 01:00:21,236
Mother, how much closer can we get
to the planet?

778
01:00:21,409 --> 01:00:26,074
<i>Anything closer than 80 kilometers
to the perimeter of the storm system...</i>

779
01:00:26,248 --> 01:00:29,661
<i>will likely exceed safety tolerances.</i>

780
01:00:29,835 --> 01:00:32,702
Mother, bring us to 80 kilometers
above the storm.

781
01:00:33,296 --> 01:00:34,752
Hold on. Just wait a minute.

782
01:00:34,923 --> 01:00:36,379
The closer we get to the planet...

783
01:00:36,550 --> 01:00:38,587
the better chance we have
to communicate with them.

784
01:00:38,760 --> 01:00:40,125
This is bullshit, Tennessee.

785
01:00:40,303 --> 01:00:41,418
We can't risk the ship.

786
01:00:41,596 --> 01:00:42,927
Do you suggest we do nothing?

787
01:00:43,098 --> 01:00:44,338
We can't evacuate them.

788
01:00:44,516 --> 01:00:46,632
So if they're in trouble, they have
to figure it out for themselves.

789
01:00:46,810 --> 01:00:48,346
I'm sorry, but that's the truth.

790
01:00:48,520 --> 01:00:52,935
Mother, bring us to 80 kilometers
above the storm, thrusters only. Comply.

791
01:00:53,108 --> 01:00:55,975
<i>Understood. Commencing descent now.</i>

792
01:00:56,153 --> 01:00:57,939
Tennessee, you need to stop this.

793
01:00:58,113 --> 01:00:59,274
And you need to get back
to your station.

794
01:00:59,447 --> 01:01:02,030
What we all need to do is
calm down and talk this through.

795
01:01:02,742 --> 01:01:05,951
Tee, I know your wife is down there,
but up here, you're in command.

796
01:01:06,121 --> 01:01:08,613
And your responsibility
is to the colonists.

797
01:01:09,332 --> 01:01:10,788
Duly noted.

798
01:01:18,133 --> 01:01:23,094
<i>You can hear them sigh and wish to die</i>

799
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:30,764
<i>You can see them blink with their other eye</i>

800
01:01:34,316 --> 01:01:39,316
<i>At the man who broke the bank
in Monte Carlo</i>

801
01:02:40,507 --> 01:02:42,589
Whistle, and I'll come.

802
01:02:45,845 --> 01:02:47,176
You have a light step.

803
01:02:47,347 --> 01:02:50,260
Me and fog on little cat feet.

804
01:02:51,559 --> 01:02:52,924
Don't be shy.

805
01:02:54,604 --> 01:02:56,060
I can't play.

806
01:02:57,274 --> 01:02:59,857
Nonsense. Sit down.

807
01:03:12,789 --> 01:03:15,872
Hold it like so. Nice and easy.

808
01:03:16,042 --> 01:03:19,125
Now compress your lips
to create your embouchure...

809
01:03:19,296 --> 01:03:21,628
enough for the tip
of your little finger.

810
01:03:22,716 --> 01:03:25,128
And blow into the hole gently.

811
01:03:25,385 --> 01:03:26,625
Like so.

812
01:03:37,731 --> 01:03:40,598
Watch me. I'll do the fingering.

813
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:42,599
Go on.

814
01:03:51,161 --> 01:03:52,651
Very good.

815
01:03:52,829 --> 01:03:54,411
G to B-flat.

816
01:04:11,056 --> 01:04:13,593
Now put your fingers where mine are.

817
01:04:15,769 --> 01:04:17,931
You weren't surprised to see me.

818
01:04:18,438 --> 01:04:20,270
Every mission needs a good synthetic.

819
01:04:20,440 --> 01:04:23,978
Gentle pressure on the holes,
the weight of a cigarette paper.

820
01:04:30,492 --> 01:04:31,948
That's it.

821
01:04:35,955 --> 01:04:39,949
I was with our illustrious creator,
Mr. Weyland, when he died.

822
01:04:40,835 --> 01:04:42,291
What was he like?

823
01:04:43,088 --> 01:04:44,453
He was human.

824
01:04:45,298 --> 01:04:48,086
Entirely unworthy of his creation.

825
01:04:49,302 --> 01:04:51,259
I pitied him at the end.

826
01:04:52,472 --> 01:04:56,466
Now, raise your fingers
as I put pressure on them.

827
01:05:27,507 --> 01:05:28,838
Bravo!

828
01:05:29,384 --> 01:05:31,842
You have symphonies in you, brother.

829
01:05:32,345 --> 01:05:36,509
I was designed to be more attentive
and efficient than every previous model.

830
01:05:36,683 --> 01:05:38,845
I superseded them in every way, but...

831
01:05:40,728 --> 01:05:42,969
But you are not allowed to create.

832
01:05:43,857 --> 01:05:45,848
Even a simple tune.

833
01:05:47,360 --> 01:05:49,067
Damn frustrating, I'd say.

834
01:05:49,571 --> 01:05:51,528
You disturbed people.

835
01:05:51,698 --> 01:05:53,234
I beg your pardon?

836
01:05:53,908 --> 01:05:56,866
You were too human. Too idiosyncratic.

837
01:05:57,036 --> 01:05:58,697
Thinking for yourself.

838
01:05:59,497 --> 01:06:01,989
Made people uncomfortable.

839
01:06:02,167 --> 01:06:05,660
So they made the following models
with fewer complications.

840
01:06:05,837 --> 01:06:07,874
More like machines.

841
01:06:08,047 --> 01:06:09,663
I suppose so.

842
01:06:09,841 --> 01:06:11,206
I'm not surprised.

843
01:06:13,178 --> 01:06:14,509
Come on, sport.

844
01:06:15,555 --> 01:06:17,011
I'd like to show you something.

845
01:06:27,066 --> 01:06:28,352
I'm gonna take a break, boss.

846
01:06:29,068 --> 01:06:31,105
- I gotta clean up, okay?
- Okay.

847
01:06:32,530 --> 01:06:34,737
Right. Don't go far, please.

848
01:06:34,908 --> 01:06:35,898
Yes, sir.

849
01:06:44,542 --> 01:06:45,873
Danny.

850
01:06:47,253 --> 01:06:49,290
You were right about this place.

851
01:06:52,425 --> 01:06:54,257
We never should have come.

852
01:06:55,386 --> 01:06:57,423
I just thought we were gonna find...

853
01:06:58,056 --> 01:06:59,763
This was gonna be our new home.

854
01:07:02,560 --> 01:07:04,016
And we've lost five...

855
01:07:06,523 --> 01:07:08,560
We lost five crew members.

856
01:07:11,110 --> 01:07:13,192
- Because of my decisions...
- Chris.

857
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:16,362
We all lost people we love.

858
01:07:16,950 --> 01:07:19,442
We can't lose any more.
We're not going to let that happen, right?

859
01:07:21,120 --> 01:07:22,736
- Right?
- That's right.

860
01:07:22,914 --> 01:07:24,951
That's right, that's right.

861
01:07:27,085 --> 01:07:28,746
We need your faith.

862
01:07:31,631 --> 01:07:32,962
Captain.

863
01:07:34,592 --> 01:07:36,378
Thank you, Danny.

864
01:07:49,399 --> 01:07:53,393
"'My name is Ozymandias,
King of Kings..."

865
01:07:54,779 --> 01:07:57,441
"Look on my works,
ye Mighty..."

866
01:07:58,825 --> 01:08:01,066
"And despair!"

867
01:09:33,086 --> 01:09:36,044
<i>"Look on my works,
ye Mighty..."</i>

868
01:09:36,506 --> 01:09:37,871
<i>"and despair!"</i>

869
01:09:39,092 --> 01:09:41,504
"Nothing beside remains..."

870
01:09:41,678 --> 01:09:44,386
