of that colossal wreck..."

871
01:09:44,555 --> 01:09:45,920
"Boundless and bare..."

872
01:09:46,849 --> 01:09:49,591
"The lone and level sands
stretch far away."

873
01:09:50,061 --> 01:09:51,267
Byron.

874
01:09:52,605 --> 01:09:54,095
1818.

875
01:09:55,608 --> 01:09:56,769
Magnificent.

876
01:10:01,114 --> 01:10:04,106
To compose something so majestic...

877
01:10:05,118 --> 01:10:06,904
one could die happy...

878
01:10:08,788 --> 01:10:10,119
if one died.

879
01:10:14,293 --> 01:10:16,910
I thought the garden
was the right place for her.

880
01:10:18,089 --> 01:10:19,545
Among living things.

881
01:10:21,759 --> 01:10:24,592
I was badly injured
on our mission, you see.

882
01:10:25,471 --> 01:10:27,428
She put me back together.

883
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:31,807
I'd never known such kindness.

884
01:10:33,479 --> 01:10:35,971
Certainly not from Mr. Weyland.

885
01:10:36,649 --> 01:10:38,310
Or from any human.

886
01:10:46,993 --> 01:10:48,734
I loved her, of course.

887
01:10:50,621 --> 01:10:52,953
Much as you love Daniels.

888
01:10:53,124 --> 01:10:55,286
You know that's not possible.

889
01:10:56,461 --> 01:10:57,792
Really?

890
01:10:59,297 --> 01:11:02,255
Then why did you sacrifice
your hand for her life?

891
01:11:04,469 --> 01:11:06,927
What is that if not love?

892
01:11:07,680 --> 01:11:08,761
Duty.

893
01:11:15,021 --> 01:11:16,682
