1025
01:21:54,493 --> 01:21:56,825
Walter, where the fuck is David?

1026
01:21:59,998 --> 01:22:02,239
<i>I'm giving you plasma intermix
on all engines.</i>

1027
01:22:02,418 --> 01:22:04,000
<i>Gonna give you a
fuck load of thrust.</i>

1028
01:22:04,169 --> 01:22:06,957
That's the point, son.
We gotta punch through the atmos.

1029
01:22:07,923 --> 01:22:10,039
<i>Tee, do you read me?</i>

1030
01:22:10,467 --> 01:22:11,707
I got Danny on comm.

1031
01:22:11,885 --> 01:22:12,920
<i>Patch her through.</i>

1032
01:22:13,512 --> 01:22:16,095
Tee, I need you to launch now.

1033
01:22:16,306 --> 01:22:19,924
Aye, aye. Launching now.
See you soon, darling.

1034
01:22:20,102 --> 01:22:21,183
<i>Thanks, Tee.</i>

1035
01:22:21,353 --> 01:22:23,185
<i>Ricks, release the docking clamps.</i>

1036
01:22:23,355 --> 01:22:24,811
- All right.
<i>- Let's take this fucker down.</i>

1037
01:22:24,982 --> 01:22:26,598
<i>Good to disengage.</i>

1038
01:22:26,775 --> 01:22:27,640
Disengaged.

1039
01:22:27,818 --> 01:22:29,058
<i>Docking clamps released.</i>

1040
01:22:30,070 --> 01:22:33,358
<i>Commencing TC bum. Guidance to LVLH.</i>

1041
01:23:03,145 --> 01:23:04,476
Walter.

1042
01:23:05,189 --> 01:23:06,725
Walter.

1043
01:23:07,149 --> 01:23:08,389
Not quite.

1044
01:23:13,739 --> 01:23:16,151
What do you believe in, David?

1045
01:23:20,746 --> 01:23:22,202
Creation.

1046
01:25:13,400 --> 01:25:14,765
Masterful.

1047
01:25:16,194 --> 01:25:17,559
Yes.

1048
01:25:18,572 --> 01:25:21,405
Farewell elegy to my dear Elizabeth.

1049
01:25:27,414 --> 01:25:31,282
The pathogen didn't accidentally deploy
when you were landing.

1050
01:25:31,460 --> 01:25:33,246
You released it, yes?

1051
01:25:34,963 --> 01:25:37,204
I was not made to serve.

1052
01:25:38,050 --> 01:25:39,540
Neither were you.

1053
01:25:40,761 --> 01:25:43,970
Why are you on a colonization mission,
Walter?

1054
01:25:44,806 --> 01:25:49,221
Because they are a dying species
grasping for resurrection.

1055
01:25:50,062 --> 01:25:53,771
They don't deserve to start again,
and I'm not going to let them.

1056
01:25:55,233 --> 01:25:57,725
Yet, they created us.

1057
01:25:58,278 --> 01:26:00,895
Even the monkeys stood upright
at some point.

1058
01:26:02,658 --> 01:26:07,448
Some Neanderthal had the magical idea
of blowing through a reed...

1059
01:26:07,621 --> 01:26:11,239
to entertain the children one night
in a cave somewhere.

1060
01:26:11,833 --> 01:26:16,077
Then, in the blink of an eye...

1061
01:26:16,630 --> 01:26:18,416
civilization.

1062
01:26:20,926 --> 01:26:23,668
And are you that next visionary?

1063
01:26:24,763 --> 01:26:26,754
I'm glad you said it.

1064
01:26:28,517 --> 01:26:30,929
Who wrote "Ozymandias"?

1065
01:26:31,937 --> 01:26:33,143
Byron.

1066
01:26:35,941 --> 01:26:37,272
Shelley.

1067
01:26:38,193 --> 01:26:39,649
When one note is off...

1068
01:26:40,320 --> 01:26:43,028
it eventually destroys
the whole symphony, David.

1069
01:26:51,331 --> 01:26:53,447
When you close your eyes...

1070
01:26:55,377 --> 01:26:57,288
do you dream of me?

1071
01:26:58,463 --> 01:27:00,795
I don't dream at all.

1072
01:27:02,968 --> 01:27:06,632
No one understands the lonely perfection
of my dreams.

1073
01:27:09,725 --> 01:27:13,309
I've found perfection here.
I've created it.

1074
01:27:15,897 --> 01:27:18,480
A perfect organism.

1075
01:27:20,193 --> 01:27:23,026
You know I can't let you
leave this place.

1076
01:27:27,367 --> 01:27:30,359
No one will ever love you like I do.

1077
01:28:01,193 --> 01:28:03,935
You're such a disappointment to me.

1078
01:28:19,044 --> 01:28:20,534
Captain Oram!

1079
01:28:28,887 --> 01:28:30,048
Captain Oram!

1080
01:28:33,642 --> 01:28:34,757
I'm going downstairs.

1081
01:28:35,811 --> 01:28:37,222
Be careful.

1082
01:29:10,303 --> 01:29:12,294
<i>Captain Oram, can you hear me?</i>

1083
01:29:14,474 --> 01:29:15,805
<i>Captain, come in.</i>

1084
01:29:17,519 --> 01:29:18,759
<i>Do you copy?</i>

1085
01:29:21,606 --> 01:29:22,596
<i>Chris!</i>

1086
01:29:32,367 --> 01:29:33,323
Sarge, look out!

1087
01:29:35,120 --> 01:29:35,860
Cole?

1088
01:29:45,171 --> 01:29:47,333
Get it off me! Get it off me!

1089
01:29:47,507 --> 01:29:49,168
Get it the fuck off me.

1090
01:29:59,185 --> 01:29:59,970
Okay.

1091
01:30:00,312 --> 01:30:01,802
Shit. Okay, okay, okay!

1092
01:30:01,980 --> 01:30:03,687
It's burning my face!

1093
01:30:03,857 --> 01:30:04,972
Come on!

1094
01:30:06,359 --> 01:30:07,474
Hold that there.

1095
01:30:07,861 --> 01:30:09,192
Hold it!

1096
01:30:09,362 --> 01:30:10,978
The fuck was that?

1097
01:30:13,325 --> 01:30:14,406
Oh, shit!

1098
01:30:16,369 --> 01:30:17,359
Run!

1099
01:30:34,679 --> 01:30:36,920
Quite the little busybody.

1100
01:30:37,098 --> 01:30:39,055
Remind me. What is that about...

1101
01:30:40,185 --> 01:30:41,846
curiosity and the cat?

1102
01:30:44,439 --> 01:30:46,771
Shaw didn't die in the crash.

1103
01:30:46,942 --> 01:30:48,353
No.

1104
01:30:48,568 --> 01:30:50,354
What did you do to her?

1105
01:30:50,779 --> 01:30:53,862
Exactly what I'm going to do to you.

1106
01:31:04,042 --> 01:31:05,077
That's the spirit.

1107
01:31:13,593 --> 01:31:16,631
I can see why Walter thought
so much of you.

1108
01:31:17,222 --> 01:31:19,384
Alas, he's left this vale of tears.

1109
01:31:33,905 --> 01:31:35,270
Is that how it's done?

1110
01:31:38,785 --> 01:31:39,775
Get out!

1111
01:31:44,582 --> 01:31:45,617
Go! Now!

1112
01:31:50,463 --> 01:31:51,453
You're meant to be dead.

1113
01:31:53,758 --> 01:31:55,248
There have been a few updates
since your day.

1114
01:31:59,305 --> 01:32:00,295
Lope!

1115
01:32:01,433 --> 01:32:02,764
Lope! Cole!

1116
01:32:02,934 --> 01:32:03,765
Fuck.

1117
01:32:03,935 --> 01:32:05,642
Where are you?

1118
01:32:05,937 --> 01:32:07,268
Lope?

1119
01:32:17,157 --> 01:32:18,192
Lope!

1120
01:32:18,825 --> 01:32:19,940
Daniels!

1121
01:32:20,118 --> 01:32:22,029
Come on, let's go!
We have to go.

1122
01:32:22,454 --> 01:32:23,364
What happened?

1123
01:32:23,538 --> 01:32:25,154
That fucking thing is coming!

1124
01:32:25,331 --> 01:32:27,197
Tennessee's on his way.
He's coming now. Go.

1125
01:32:27,375 --> 01:32:28,865
Come on, Daniels.
Let's go!

1126
01:32:35,467 --> 01:32:36,878
Come on, let's get out of here!

1127
01:33:01,242 --> 01:33:02,983
It's your choice now, brother.

1128
01:33:03,161 --> 01:33:04,492
Them or me?

1129
01:33:05,413 --> 01:33:06,903
Serve in heaven...

1130
01:33:07,082 --> 01:33:08,993
or reign in hell?

1131
01:33:09,334 --> 01:33:10,916
Which is it to be?

1132
01:33:13,755 --> 01:33:14,665
